text: Falmouth (meaning mouth of the River Fal) is a town on the south coast of Cornwall. The A39 road links Falmouth with North Devon. In 2001 there were 20,775 people living in Falmouth. Falmouth harbour is a large natural harbour and Carrick Roads are nearby. Carrick Roads are the estuary of the River Fal. The MP for Falmouth is Sarah Newton, a Tory. The school there is Falmouth School. == References == Category:Towns in Cornwall Category:Port cities and towns of England Category:Civil parishes in Cornwall
